## Accessibility

### VoiceOver Support

If Then Reset is fully compatible with VoiceOver:
- All buttons and controls are properly labeled
- Feeling types include descriptive labels
- Reset techniques include instructions
- History entries are readable with context

**To enable VoiceOver:**
1. Go to Settings > Accessibility > VoiceOver
2. Toggle VoiceOver on

### Reduce Motion

For users sensitive to motion or animations:

1. Open **About & Settings** in the app
2. Enable **Reduce Motion/Animations**
3. This disables most app animations

Alternatively, use iOS system settings:
- Settings > Accessibility > Motion > Reduce Motion

### Dynamic Type Support

If Then Reset respects iOS Dynamic Type settings for larger text:
1. Go to Settings > Accessibility > Display & Text Size
2. Adjust text size to your preference
3. App text will scale accordingly

### Color & Contrast

- High contrast mode compatible
- Readable color schemes for color blindness
- Clear visual hierarchy

